    "created_at": "2018-06-14T19:52:50Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-06-14T19:52:50Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Making servers restartable might be complicated by the current server lifecycle and the fact that servers get created, then ports get added to them, then they get started, and then they get stopped.\r\n\r\nShould a server hang onto its ports after being stopped just in case it gets started again? I suspect not. Should a server remember on which ports it was serving before and attempt to serve on those ports again when it is restarted?\r\n\r\nHow painful today is working around the lack of server restarting? What use cases would server restarting benefit if implemented?"
  },
